,"name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_top-left_header","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_top-left_header_all-caps","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"LET’S INVESTIGATE"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_header_separator","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"|"}]},{"type":"text","text":"  WEEK 1: Five Senses"}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"circle-time-section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_no_paragraph_rule_day_2","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Share the Mind Builder: Focus Attention"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Remind children that they can focus their attention on something and try not to get distracted. Show children the picture sides of Alphabet Cards from Aa to Ll. Hold each card up for a second, and then ask: "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher_talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Were you paying attention? What did you see?"}]},{"type":"text","text":" After using the cards, ask children to tell what, if anything distracted them and caused them to look away. "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_icon"}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_no_paragraph_rule_day_2","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Focus on Vocabulary"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Introduce two new vocabulary words. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Use 3.1.2 Vocabulary Cards."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_vocab_words","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"explains imagine"}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"story-time-section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_no_paragraph_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Connect to the Book"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Show the book cover."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Today we are going to think about the Focus Attention Mind Builder. As we revisit "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_emphasis_non-ital","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Close Your Eyes"}]},{"type":"text","text":" by Victoria Pérez Escrivá, let’s pay attention to what each brother says. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Use the Clifford Puppet."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Clifford loves this book because it shows how two children describe things in different ways."}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_with_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Close-Read: Connect to the Mind Builder"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Read aloud the book and the Day 2 prompts. Use the Equity Sticks during reading to choose children to answer questions."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"pages 4–5"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Let’s pay attention. One brother explains that a tree is a big stick that comes out of the earth.  Which part of the tree do you think he was touching when he said that? "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_routine_bold","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"(MB)"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_icon"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Revisit "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_highlight_teacher_inst_Italic","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"explains"}]},{"type":"text","text":" Vocabulary Card."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"pages 6–7"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Let’s pay attention to what he says now. He says that a snake is a cold, smooth rope. Which part of the snake do you think he was touching when he said that? "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_routine_bold","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"(MB)"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_icon"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"pages 8–9"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Let’s think about what he says now. He says that a heart-shaped clock is a little box with a heart inside. What do you think he    was hearing when he said that? "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_routine_bold","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"(MB)"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_icon"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"pages 16–17"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"One brother says the moon is a whole bunch of crickets. Close your eyes and imagine you hear a whole bunch of crickets. Is it noisy or quiet?"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Revisit "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_highlight_teacher_inst_Italic","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"imagine"}]},{"type":"text","text":" Vocabulary Card."}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_with_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Extended Play"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Play “What’s Missing?” Invite children to sit in a circle. Present five objects, such as a crayon, scissors, ruler, chalk, and marker. Name each one as you place it in the circle. Ask children to close and hide their eyes. Remove one item and hide it. Have children open their eyes and ask, “What’s missing?” Return the item and repeat, removing a different item each time. Gradually add additional items to engage children’s visual memory and engage their ability to pay attention. "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_routine_bold","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"(MB)"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_icon"}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_with_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Shared Writing"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Transcribe children’s speech as they talk about what things they use their ears to hear. [Note: revise for children with auditory impairments.]"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"child-development-section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_hed-green","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Child Development: Mind Builder"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_body","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Focusing one’s attention is a basic executive function skill that children need to develop in order to begin learning. Children must work through several steps to successfully pay attention: 1) be alert, 2) select what to pay attention to and sustain that attention even with outside distractions, and 3) if distracted, shift focus back to task. (Rosen/Understood.org)"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"day_3","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"week","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_top-left_header","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_top-left_header_all-caps","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"LET’S INVESTIGATE"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_header_separator","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"|"}]},{"type":"text","text":"  WEEK 1: Five Senses"}]}]}]},{"type":"e