,"name":"rac_teacher-talk_emphasis_non-ital","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Close Your Eyes"}]},{"type":"text","text":" by Victoria Pérez Escrivá."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Use the Pablo Stick Puppet."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Pablo loves this book. Thinking about our senses makes him feel like a scientist!"}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_with_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Share the Guiding Question"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"This week, we read about two brothers. We found out that the brother who could not see used his other senses. He could hear, touch, and smell things. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Now, I want you to think about this Guiding Question:"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_guiding-question_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"How do our senses help us learn?"}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_with_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Read-Aloud: Retell and Reenact"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Reread and retell the book together. Use Equity Sticks to choose children to actively participate in the prompts below."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"pages 6–7"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"You can see a snake slither. Use your arm and show me how a snake slithers. "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_icon"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"pages 8–9"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"We can listen to a clock tick tock. What sound do you hear at the beginning of the word "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_emphasis_non-ital","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"listen"}]},{"type":"text","text":"? What letter make the /l/ sound? What sound do you hear at the end of "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_emphasis_non-ital","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"ticktock"}]},{"type":"text","text":"? What letter makes the /k/sound?"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Let’s all make the sound of a clock tick-tocking."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"pages 12–13"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"You can touch and smell soap. Let’s pretend we have a bar of soap. Let’s wet it and make lather. Let’s wash our hands and dry them. Finally, let’s smell our hands to see how good they smell. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"pages 16–17, 21"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Close your eyes. Pretend you’re falling asleep. You can hear crickets singing. Let’s chirp like the crickets in the night. Now whisper to a friend and say, “Good night!”"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Revisit "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_highlight_teacher_inst_Italic","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"whispers"}]},{"type":"text","text":" Vocabulary Card."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"page 25"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"What does his mother tell the brother to do? Now close your eyes. Listen! What do you hear? "}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_with_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Talk About It"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Invite children to turn and talk for a moment about the Guiding Question: "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_guiding-question_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"How do our senses help us learn?"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Give time for "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_routine_bold","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Turn and Talk"}]},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Then, use the Equity Sticks to choose two or three children to share their responses."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Possible responses:"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_bulleted","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Our hands let us touch things."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_bulleted","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Our noses let us smell things."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_bulleted","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Our eyes let us see how things look."}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_with_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Independent Writing"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Invite children to draw or write about how they use one of their senses."}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_support_challenge","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_support_challenge-box","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_hed_support-challenge","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Support"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_support_numbers","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"1"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Does your nose help you smell things? "}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_support_challenge-box","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_support_numbers","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"2"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"My nose helps me sm"},{"type":"element","name":"fill-in-the-blank","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"_____"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_emphasis_non-ital","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"(smell)"}]},{"type":"text","text":" things. "}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_support_challenge-box","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_support_numbers","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"3"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"My nose helps me smell things."}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_support_challenge-box","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_hed_support-challenge","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Challenge"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"What senses have you used today? "}]}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"child-development-section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_hed-green","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Child Development: Gross Motor Skills"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_body","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Gross motor skills are important to children’s physical development. Activities, such as scarf dancing, that require large muscle movement help build these skills in children. Gross motor abilities impact children’s success in school and in participating in everyday functions, such as sitting upright, writing and drawing, and playing sports."}]}]}]}]}]}]}]